Global Wet-laid Non-woven Fabrics Market Insights
Wet-laid Non-woven Fabrics Market size was valued at USD 4.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 6.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Wet-laid Non-woven Fabrics Market Overview
The global Wet-laid Non-woven Fabrics Market was valued at approximately USD 3.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 5.8 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% during the forecast period. Wet-laid non-woven fabrics are widely used in industries such as automotive, medical, hygiene, and filtration. The demand for these fabrics is driven by their superior performance, eco-friendly nature, and versatile applications across various end-use industries. With increasing awareness regarding sustainability and the need for efficient production processes, the market for wet-laid non-woven fabrics is experiencing robust growth globally.

